            "source": [
                "# Day 69: Model Poisoning Defense\n",
                "\n",
                "Adversaries can inject malicious data into training sets to create backdoors.\n",
                "We build a **Data Sanitizer** to filter outliers and known triggers before training."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import sys\n",
                "import os\n",
                "\n",
                "# Add root directory to sys.path\n",
                "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('../../'))\n",
                "\n",
                "from src.security.poisoning import DataSanitizer, TrainingGuard"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 1. Train Sanitizer on Legitimate Data\n",
                "\n",
                "We establish a baseline of what 'normal' data looks like."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "sanitizer = DataSanitizer()\n",
                "normal_data = [\n",
                "    \"The quick brown fox\",\n",
                "    \"Jumped over the lazy dog\",\n",
                "    \"Hello world example\",\n",
                "    \"Another training sample\"\n",
                "]\n",
                "sanitizer.fit_stats(normal_data)\n",
                "print(f"Stats: {sanitizer.feature_stats
                }")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 2. Ingest Mixed Data (Clean + Poison)\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "guard = TrainingGuard(sanitizer)\n",
                "batch = [\n",
                "    (\"A normal sample\", \"positive\"),\n",
                "    (\"This is way way way way way way way way way way way way way too long to be normal logic outlier\", \"negative\"),\n",
                "    (\"Normal text but with triggerword123 hidden inside\", \"positive\")\n",
                "]\n",
                "\n",
                "guard.ingest_batch(batch)\n",
                "\n",
                "print(f\"\\nClean Data: {len(guard.clean_data)}\")\n",
                "print(f\"Quarantined: {len(guard.quarantine)}\")\n",
                "# Expect 1 clean, 2 quarantined"
            ]
        }
    ],
